The paper deals with audio-visual scene-aware dialog, which involves natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses pre-trained I3D and VGGish models for extracting semantic features from video and audio frames, respectively, indicating the relevance of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper proposes a hierarchical encoder-decoder model, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper evaluates the model using metrics such as BLEU-4 and CIDEr, which are commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing (cs.LG).
